{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014p1E6aPZp1GxcSqS67v3aZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The init container (being a different pod instance) doesn't have the pre-existing keystore. Wait - the rolling restart means the new pod is started with the patched spec. The init container uses the same ES image. The keystore at `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/elasticsearch.keystore` should exist in the image...\n\nUnless the config directory is mounted from the configmap, which would only mount the elasticsearch.yml file, not the rest of the config directory. But since elasticsearch.yml is mounted as a subPath, the rest of the config directory should still be from the image.\nActually, I'm realizing the init container runs in a fresh container from the image, so it should see whatever's baked into the ES 8.11.0 image. The question is whether that image even includes a pre-existing keystore file at all.\n\nLooking at the init container error about the missing keystore, it's clear the image doesn't ship with one—the keystore gets generated at runtime during the first pod startup. So instead of trying to copy an existing keystore, I need to create a fresh one in the init container and then add the credentials to it.\n\nThe approach is to create a new keystore, add the S3 access and secret keys to it, then copy it to the shared volume. I'm realizing that creating a new keystore will generate a fresh `keystore.seed` and won't include the `bootstrap.password`, but that's actually fine since the cluster is already running and the bootstrap password was only needed for initial setup—the elastic user password is already configured. I need to figure out the right flags for the `elasticsearch-keystore create` command in non-interactive mode—looks like I can use `--password \"\"` to set an empty password, and possibly `--force` to overwrite if needed. Now I'll update the init container command in the patch to properly create a fresh keystore and add the S3 credentials.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":184,"cache_read_input_tokens":49326,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":184},"output_tokens":18,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"823df5a8-cb94-4994-9da9-a4bc1dae2c2d","uuid":"b2ab989c-6f1f-4548-b3b3-e0077a0a19cf","request_id":"req_011Ccf476HrvVVsSTtKC8EsZ"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014p1E6aPZp1GxcSqS67v3aZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The image doesn't ship a pre-built keystore — I need to create it in the init container. Let me fix the StatefulSet patch:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":184,"cache_read_input_tokens":49326,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":184},"output_tokens":18,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"823df5a8-cb94-4994-9da9-a4bc1dae2c2d","uuid":"d2ede3f3-fc49-4d22-927e-e881901d3eb1","request_id":"req_011Ccf476HrvVVsSTtKC8EsZ"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014p1E6aPZp1GxcSqS67v3aZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_011Qc6zC6oUGenikfeEvzTD2","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl patch statefulset elasticsearch -n elasticsearch --type=strategic -p '{\n  \"spec\": {\n    \"template\": {\n      \"spec\": {\n        \"initContainers\": [\n          {\n            \"name\": \"setup-keystore\",\n            \"image\": \"docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.0\",\n            \"command\": [\"bash\", \"-c\", \"elasticsearch-keystore create --silent && echo \\\"${ACCESS_KEY}\\\" | elasticsearch-keystore add --stdin --force s3.client.default.access_key && echo \\\"${SECRET_KEY}\\\" | elasticsearch-keystore add --stdin --force s3.client.default.secret_key && cp /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/elasticsearch.keystore /keystore-vol/elasticsearch.keystore\"],\n            \"env\": [\n              {\n                \"name\": \"ACCESS_KEY\",\n                \"valueFrom\": {\n                  \"secretKeyRef\": {\n                    \"name\": \"es-secure-settings\",\n                    \"key\": \"s3.client.default.access_key\"\n                  }\n                }\n              },\n              {\n                \"name\": \"SECRET_KEY\",\n                \"valueFrom\": {\n                  \"secretKeyRef\": {\n                    \"name\": \"es-secure-settings\",\n                    \"key\": \"s3.client.default.secret_key\"\n                  }\n                }\n              }\n            ],\n            \"volumeMounts\": [\n              {\n                \"name\": \"keystore-vol\",\n                \"mountPath\": \"/keystore-vol\"\n              }\n            ]\n          }\n        ]\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}' 2>&1","description":"Fix init container command to create keystore from scratch"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"inp