{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01BgZ8FpQdPXAm2oPJxPXAo4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"AH-HA! Found it!\n\nThe pod still has BOTH volumeMounts:\n1. `keystore-vol` subPath `elasticsearch.keystore` → `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/elasticsearch.keystore`\n2. `keystore-vol` → `/keystore-source`\n\nMy Python patch removed the subPath mount and added the `/keystore-source` mount. But looking at the pod spec, BOTH mounts are still there! This means my Python patch didn't fully apply, or there's some old pod spec.\n\nThis is why `cp` says \"same file\" — because `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/elasticsearch.keystore` is the same emptyDir file (via subPath mount) as `/keystore-source/elasticsearch.keystore` (via regular mount). They're literally the same inode on the same emptyDir!\nThe kubectl apply didn't fully remove the old subPath mount, so I need to export the current StatefulSet spec and apply a clean version that completely removes the conflicting mount.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":971,"cache_read_input_tokens":66160,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":971},"output_tokens":31,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"823df5a8-cb94-4994-9da9-a4bc1dae2c2d","uuid":"691eb3da-b1eb-40da-931a-7601b51ef53c","request_id":"req_011Ccf4VMhvaptdPTxMGgCnQ"}
