{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01N6tkj6nEzifpMs6GCM5u5f","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `es-data-new` StatefulSet uses a different configmap: `es-config-new`. I need to update `es-config-new` with the S3 client settings and also add keystore credentials to `es-data-new-0` and `es-data-new-1`.\n\nAlso, the `es-data-new` StatefulSet has no `data` PVC volume (based on the volumes list I see - it only has `config` and `certs`). Hmm, but data pods typically need persistent storage...\n\nWait, the rolling restart of `es-data-new` would cause issues if the pods have no PVC. \n\nLet me check if they have a `volumeClaimTemplates` entry. For the S3 client settings, since they're static and require a restart, I'd need to update the `es-config-new` configmap and restart the pods—but that's risky without persistent storage. Alternatively, I could just update the keystore on the pods and call reload_secure_settings, though the endpoint settings like `s3.client.default.endpoint` and `s3.client.default.protocol` would still need a restart to take effect.\n\nLet me look at what's actually in the es-config-new configmap.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":945,"cache_read_input_tokens":106721,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":945},"output_tokens":31,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"823df5a8-cb94-4994-9da9-a4bc1dae2c2d","uuid":"ae1936f7-26f2-4ba7-8b6d-f3505b73194e","request_id":"req_011Ccf5rkkxg8XYHEReCxJ5Y"}
