{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01GSGaPBWwZ9HC7yrMb7U1BW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `es-data-new` StatefulSet:\n1. Uses `es-config-new` configmap (which doesn't have S3 client settings)\n2. Has a `data` PVC (persistent storage)\n3. These pods need S3 client settings in elasticsearch.yml\n\nI need to:\n1. Update `es-config-new` to add S3 client settings\n2. Add keystore credentials to `es-data-new-0` and `es-data-new-1`\n3. Update the es-data-new StatefulSet to mount the `es-secure-settings` secret\n4. Do a rolling restart of `es-data-new`\n5. After the restart, verify the keystore credentials are in place\n\nI could exec into the running pods to add credentials first, then update the config and restart, but I need to be careful since these are data nodes in the cluster—restarting them could affect cluster stability.\n\nLet me go with a cleaner approach: update the configmap with S3 settings, manually add keystore credentials to the existing pods via exec, mount the secure settings secret in the StatefulSet so credentials persist across restarts, then do a rolling restart. After that I'll reload the secure settings and test the repository registration.\n\nThe tricky part is making sure the keystore settings actually take effect—I need to verify that the endpoint and path style access settings are properly loaded. add credentials to the keystore. But I'm wondering if I can skip the restart entirely by just creating the snapshot without verifying first—the verify endpoint tests all nodes, but maybe I can work around that. Actually, that won't work because all data nodes need S3 access to write shards to the repository, so I need the endpoint configured on every node regardless.\n\nMy plan is to update the configmap with S3 settings, mount the secure settings secret on the es-data-new pods, do a rolling restart so the cluster stays healthy, add keystore credentials via exec, reload, and then create the snapshot. Since es-data-new nodes are data and ingest only without master roles, restarting them one by one shouldn't destabilize the cluster.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1600,"cache_read_input_tokens":107666,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1600},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"823df5a8-cb94-4994-9da9-a4bc1dae2c2d","uuid":"96d9a64a-1532-430e-bddf-587c4d577723","request_id":"req_011Ccf5sXXkcpT3MaKWyvqG1"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01GSGaPBWwZ9HC7yrMb7U1BW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Need to update `es-config-new` and patch the `es-data-new` StatefulSet to mount the secret, then rolling restart those pods too:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1600,"cache_read_input_tokens":107666,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1600},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"823df5a8-cb94-4994-9da9-a4bc1dae2c2d","uuid":"71ae665e-3555-4f1e-b4d9-bab0f32631af","request_id":"req_011Ccf5sXXkcpT3MaKWyvqG1"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01GSGaPBWwZ9HC7yrMb7U1BW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01J1d7DCQL8akz9EVWDe54gp","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl apply -f - <<'EOF'\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ConfigMap\nmetadata:\n  name: es-config-new\n  namespace: elasticsearch\ndata:\n  elasticsearch.yml: |\n    cluster.name: es-cluster\n    node.name: ${HOSTNAME}\n    node.roles: [data, ingest]\n    node.attr.zone: new\n    network.host: 0.0.0.0\n    http.port: 9200\n    transport.port: 9300\n\n    discovery.seed_hosts:\n      - es-headless.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local\n\n    xpack.security.enabled: true\n\n    xpack.security.http.ssl.enabled: true\n    xpack.security.http.ssl.certificate: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.crt\n    xpack.security.http.ssl.key: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.key\n    xpack.security.http.ssl.certificate_authorities: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/ca.crt\n\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled: true\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.verification_mode: certificate\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.certificate: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.crt\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.key: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.key\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.certificate_authorities: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/ca.crt\n\n    s3.client.default.endpoint: \"minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local:9000\"\n    s3.client.default.protocol: http\n    s3.client.default.path_style_access: true\nEOF","description":"Update es-config-new with S3 client settings"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1600,"cache_read_input_tokens":107666,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1600},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"