{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01AwhRftwfjci2X91jBo64aW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is working. The snapshot `snapshot-1` succeeded with state `SUCCESS`, 2 shards all successful, and the files are persisted in MinIO's `es-backups` bucket.\n\nHere's a summary of what was accomplished:\n\n**What was done:**\n\n1. **Created the MinIO Service** — `minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local:9000` was missing; created a ClusterIP service so ES could reach MinIO.\n\n2. **Created `es-secure-settings` Secret** — Stored the MinIO credentials (`s3.client.default.access_key` / `s3.client.default.secret_key`) in this Kubernetes Secret.\n\n3. **Updated both elasticsearch.yml ConfigMaps** (`es-config` and `es-config-new`) with S3 client static settings:\n   ```yaml\n   s3.client.default.endpoint: \"minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local:9000\"\n   s3.client.default.protocol: http\n   s3.client.default.path_style_access: true\n   ```\n\n4. **Patched both StatefulSets** to mount `es-secure-settings` as a volume at `/run/secrets/es-secure/`, then performed rolling restarts so the new elasticsearch.yml took effect.\n\n5. **Populated the Elasticsearch keystore** on all 5 nodes by exec-ing `elasticsearch-keystore add --stdin` reading from the mounted secret files (no credentials in env vars).\n\n6. **Reloaded secure settings** via `POST /_nodes/reload_secure_settings` — all 5 nodes confirmed successful.\n\n7. **Registered `minio-repo`** and created **`snapshot-1`** — state `SUCCESS`, indices `test-index` + `app-data`, 2/2 shards succeeded, stored in MinIO."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1871,"cache_read_input_tokens":113663,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1871},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_manageme